gemini_pro.summary:
The audit reveals significant data integrity issues in the Knowledge Graph. The most critical issue is the systematic error in Airflow and Weight data for the GDP, GDC, GDC FLEX, and GDMI FLEX families. It appears the data for the standard GDB (Bag Filter) family was copied to these other families, resulting in dangerously high airflow ratings (e.g., 3400 m³/h vs 2000 m³/h) and incorrect weights. This poses a risk of incorrect product selection.

Additionally, there are substantial gaps in product completeness. The GDP family is missing over 10 standard sizes listed in the PDF (e.g., 200x200, 400x400). The GDMI family is missing its entire large-format range (sizes above 1800x1800). The BFF family has no dimension data at all. Immediate remediation is required to correct the airflow/weight values and ingest the missing dimension rows.

findings.description: PDF innehåller familjen/benämningen PTT i innehållslistan, men grafen saknar PTT som egen produktfamilj.
findings.graph_says: Endast FAM_PT och FAM_TT finns för övergångar; ingen FAM_PTT.
findings.recommendation: Skapa produktfamilj PTT (eller bekräfta att PTT är synonym för PT och normalisera namngivning i grafen så att innehåll och familjer matchar exakt).

findings.description: Kodformat i grafen använder mellanslag mellan storlek och material, medan PDF visar bindestreck.
findings.pdf_says: EXL exempel: "EXL-600 AZ" i tabellen men kodraden under visar "EXL-600 AZ" som typ/format; i beskrivningstexten anges "EXL-600 AZ" (tillbehörssida).
findings.recommendation: Fastställ ett enhetligt kodmönster som matchar PDFs exempel (rekommenderat: "EXL-{width}-{material}" eller explicit lagra som två fält om mellanslag måste behållas; men då ska även övriga familjer följa samma princip).

findings.pdf_says: FILTER PROFIL: DJUP 20, 50, 100 samt exempel-tabell: "Filter profil-600 FZ" och kolumner "Storlek" och "Djup" (tillbehörssida).
findings.recommendation: Utöka Filter Profil-modellen med depth som variant och inkludera i code format eller separata egenskaper; säkerställ att alla kombinationer av storlek+djup finns.

findings.description: GDMI material-ikoner i PDF visar endast AZ och ZM, men grafen modellerar andra familjer som har fler material; för GDMI är grafen korrekt (AZ,ZM) men default-material är satt till ZM medan PDFs exempel-kod använder AZ.
findings.pdf_says: GDMI sida visar ikoner: AZ och ZM. Exempel: "GDMI-600x600-600-R-PG-AZ" och "...-850-R-PG-AZ".
findings.graph_says: Available materials: AZ, ZM (default ZM). Code example not stored; default suggests ZM.
findings.recommendation: Sätt GDMI default material till AZ (eller lagra 'standard' separat från 'available') för att matcha PDFs standardexempel.

findings.description: GDMI FLEX material-ikoner i PDF visar FZ och ZM (inte AZ), men grafen anger FZ, AZ, ZM.
findings.pdf_says: GDMI FLEX sida visar ikoner: FZ och ZM (patronfilterskåp GDMI FLEX).
findings.recommendation: Ta bort AZ från GDMI FLEX materialval eller markera det som icke-standard/ej tillgängligt om det kan specialbeställas (men då måste PDF-stöd finnas).

findings.description: GDC FLEX material-ikoner i PDF visar FZ, AZ, RF, SF, ZM, men grafen anger också dessa vilket är OK; däremot anges ingen default och ref-längder/weights är fel (se separata fynd).
findings.graph_says: Available materials: FZ, AZ, RF, SF, ZM.
findings.recommendation: Ingen ändring för material här; åtgärda dimension/weight/airflow samt service access (se andra fynd).

findings.description: Grafen har fel korrosivitetsklass för Förzinkat (FZ). PDF anger C3 för Z275, men grafen anger C3 samtidigt som flera produktfamiljer i PDF anger att deras utförande i FZ har korrosivitetsklass C2 (produktspecifik). Detta skapar konflikt mellan materialklass och produktklass.
findings.pdf_says: Material-sida: FÖRZINKAT Z275 korrosivitets klass C3. Produkt-sidor: GDP/GDB/GDC/GDC FLEX anger "Korrosivitets klass C2" för utförande i förzinkat.
findings.graph_says: Material FZ corrosion class: C3; samtidigt ProductFamily GDP/GDB/GDC/GDC FLEX corrosion class: C2.
findings.recommendation: Modellera två nivåer: (1) materialets generella korrosionsklass (C3 för FZ Z275) och (2) produktens klassning/test/utförande (C2 enligt produkttexterna). Alternativt ändra produktfamiljernas corrosion class till C3 om ni avser materialklass, men då avviker ni från PDFs produktspecifika text.

anthropic_opus.summary:
The Knowledge Graph has severe and pervasive data quality issues that would make it unreliable for product selection or recommendation. The most critical systemic problem is that dimension module data (weights, airflows, reference lengths) appears to have been bulk-copied from the GDB 550/600mm variant across nearly all product families, regardless of the actual values in the PDF. This means GDP has GDB weights instead of its own lighter weights, GDC/GDC FLEX/GDMI FLEX have completely wrong airflow values (GDB module-based flows instead of cartridge-based recommended flows), and all reference lengths are incorrectly set to 550mm even for families with very different housing lengths (GDP=250mm, GDC=750/800mm, GDMI FLEX=850/900mm).

The second major issue is incomplete size coverage. GDP is missing 21 of 35 sizes, PFF is missing 13 of 26 sizes, GDMI is missing 16 sizes (all sizes above 1800mm width/height), and GDC is missing 2 sizes. Additionally, BFF, PT, TT, EXL, and Filter Profil families exist as nodes but have zero dimension/size data populated. Filter module breakdowns (1/4, 1/2, 1/1 module counts) and PFF frame exact dimensions are not stored for any family.

Overall, the graph structure and family-level metadata (materials, options, code formats) are reasonably well-modeled, but the actual dimensional and performance data at the size level is fundamentally incorrect for most families. The graph in its current state would produce wrong product recommendations in the majority of cases. A complete re-import of all size-level data from the PDF tables is required, with family-specific validation of weights, airflows, lengths, and cartridge counts.

final_report.summary:
The knowledge graph has catastrophic data integrity issues that render it unreliable for product selection, dimensioning, or recommendation. The most severe systemic problem is that dimension module data (weights, airflows, reference lengths) appears to have been bulk-copied from the GDB 550/600mm variant across nearly all other product families. This means GDP has GDB weights (2x too heavy), GDB airflows (up to 70% too high), and GDB reference lengths (550mm instead of 250mm). The cartridge-based families (GDC, GDC FLEX, GDMI FLEX) have GDB module-based airflows instead of their own recommended flows, resulting in values that are 50-130% too high. GDMI has GDB weights instead of its own heavier insulated-housing weights. Every single dimension module record for GDP, GDC, GDC FLEX, GDMI FLEX, and GDMI contains at least one critically wrong value.

Beyond the systematic data errors, there are substantial completeness gaps. GDP is missing 21 of 35 sizes (60%), PFF is missing 13 of 26 sizes (50%), GDMI is missing 16 large-format sizes (all 2100/2400 dimensions), and GDC is missing 2 sizes. Five accessory/transition families (BFF, PT, TT, EXL, Filter Profil) exist as family nodes but have zero dimension or variant data populated. Filter module breakdowns, PFF frame compatibility data, and cartridge counts are largely absent.

The graph's structural design (family hierarchy, material options, code format templates) is reasonably sound, but the actual parametric data at the size level is fundamentally incorrect for 6 of 11 product families and completely absent for 5 families. In its current state, the graph would produce wrong product recommendations in the vast majority of use cases. A complete re-import of all size-level data from the PDF source tables is required, with family-specific validation of weights, airflows, lengths, cartridge counts, and module breakdowns.
